Now, let us compute the difference in the EPS of the company:
 &nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{EPS}&=\text{Actual EPS}-\text{2017 Projections}\\[12pt]
&={\$7.93}-{\$8.16}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$(0.23)}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The difference in the EPS of the company between the actual EPS in the website and the projected EPS for the current year is \$(0.23) which is considered insignificant.**
  .

Now, let us compute the difference in the EPS of the company:
 &nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{EPS}&=\text{Actual EPS}-\text{2018 Projections}\\[12pt]
&={\$8.89}-{\$8.62}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$0.27}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The difference in the EPS of the company between the actual EPS in the website and the projected EPS for the next year is \$0.27 which is considered insignificant.**
